    <h4>🔍 How to check if a source is trustworthy:</h4>
    <div class="trust-row"><span class="icon">👤</span><div><strong>Who wrote it?</strong> Look for a government, museum, university, or named expert. If there's no author, be careful.</div></div>
    <div class="trust-row"><span class="icon">📅</span><div><strong>Is it up to date?</strong> Check for a date on the page. Older pages about recent events can have wrong information.</div></div>
    <div class="trust-row"><span class="icon">🔁</span><div><strong>Does it match other sources?</strong> If two or three trusted sources say the same thing, it's more likely to be true.</div></div>
    <div class="trust-row"><span class="icon">💰</span><div><strong>Is someone trying to sell you something?</strong> Websites trying to sell products may not give balanced information.</div></div>
